                <p>Another resource contained in this website is how MBE and MIL-STD-31000A relate to the goals of Better Buying Power 2.0. Through the focus on the updated TDP, a dividend is achieved when the best practices of MIL-STD-31000A are applied to the mandates of BBP 2.0, which are to strengthen DOD&rsquo;s buying power, improve industry productivity, and provide an affordable, value-added military capability to the warfighter. </p>
                <p>To view the article entitled &ldquo;Using MIL-STD-31000A to Support Better Buying Power 2.0&rdquo; published in the October 2013 issue of Contract Management Magazine</p>
                <p><a href="http://www.transcendata.com/company/media/news/iti/articles/Using-MIL-STD-31000a-to-Support-BBP-20-CM-published-article.pdf" target="_new" class="button purple">Click Here</a></p>
                <p>For a link to the Better Buying Power 2.0 memorandum and please click here </p>
                <p><a href="http://www.acq.osd.mil/docs/USD(ATL) Signed Memo to Workforce BBP 2 0 (13 Nov 12) with attachments.pdf" target="_new" class="button purple">Click Here</a></p>
                <p>Interim Department of Defense Instruction (DoDI) 5000.02 was issued on November 25, 2013.  It states that &ldquo;The Acquisition Strategy will address how program management will create and sustain a competitive environment, from program inception through sustainment.  Strategies to be considered include:  competitive prototyping, dual sourcing, open systems architecture that enable competition for upgrades, acquisition of complete technical data packages, and competition at the subsystem level.&rdquo;</p>
